main event: A civilian observed a bright light in the sky over Winona, Mississippi on October 26, 1966.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 4 hours, The object was seen moving slowly upward and to the west, The witness reported seeing the object for at least 2 weeks, The object was described as brighter than average but dimmer than the sun, The object did not make any sound during the observation.
sighted object: a bright light in the sky
witness description: A civilian familiar with most projects in Dreamwood, Mississippi.
